    "abstract": "<jats:p>\n                  We report the kinetics of the immune response in relation to clinical and virological features of a patient with mild-to-moderate coronavirus disease-19 (COVID-19) requiring hospitalisation. Increased antibody-secreting cells, follicular T-helper cells, activated CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  and CD8\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T-cells and IgM/IgG SARS-CoV-2-binding antibodies were detected in blood, prior to symptomatic recovery. These immunological changes persisted for at least 7 days following full resolution of symptoms, indicating substantial anti-viral immunity in this non-severe COVID-19.\n                </jats:p>",
    "DOI": "10.1101/2020.02.20.20025841",
